# React Functional Patterns Best Practices

Preferred patterns for React functional components and hooks. Project rule **react-component-conventions.mdc** defines file structure and library usage; this rule adds ordering and patterns.

## Functional Component Syntax

Use functional components. Prefer named exports. Return type can be `JSX.Element` or `JSX.Element | null`:

```tsx
// Preferred
export const ComponentName = ({ prop1, prop2 }): JSX.Element => {
  return <div>Content</div>;
};

// May return null
export const ConditionalComponent = (): JSX.Element | null => {
  if (someCondition) return null;
  return <div>Content</div>;
};
```

## Hooks Organization

Order hooks in a logical sequence:

```tsx
export const Component = ({ initialData }): JSX.Element => {
  // 1. State hooks first
  const [data, setData] = useState(initialData);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);

  // 2. Ref hooks
  const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);

  // 3. Context hooks
  const { user } = useUserContext();

  // 4. Custom hooks
  const { isSmallScreen } = useResponsive();

  // 5. Data fetching or derived values (useMemo)
  const filteredData = useMemo(() => data.filter((item) => item.isActive), [data]);

  // 6. Effect hooks last
  useEffect(() => { /* ... */ }, [dependencies]);

  // 7. Event handlers and other functions
  const handleClick = () => { /* ... */ };

  // 8. Return JSX
  return <div>{/* Content */}</div>;
};
```

## Callback Functions

Use appropriate callback patterns:

```tsx
// Functions that don't need dependencies — define outside component
const formatDate = (date: Date): string => date.toLocaleDateString();

export const Component = (): JSX.Element => {
  // Handlers that use state/props — use useCallback when passed to children
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => { /* ... */ }, [dependencies]);

  // Simple handlers — can be inline
  const handleToggle = () => { /* ... */ };

  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>;
};
```

## Conditional Rendering

Prefer clear patterns: early returns for loading/error, then main content.

## List Rendering

Use stable, unique keys. Prefer `item.id`; use index only when list is static and documented.

## Error Handling

Use error boundaries for child trees. For async operations, set error state in catch and render error UI. Clean up effects (see async-effect-patterns.mdc).

## Accessibility

Use semantic HTML and ARIA where needed (see a11y-standards.mdc): `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, `aria-hidden`, `aria-labelledby`.

## Prop Handling

Destructure props with defaults where it improves readability.

## Clean Up Effects

Always clean up side effects (subscriptions, timers, AbortController). See **async-effect-patterns.mdc** for async useEffect patterns.
